<Font opaque="true" background="[0,255,0]">v) Use Maple to augment the matrix <Font bold="true">A</Font> by a suitable identity matrix and use Gauss-Jordan elimination to again find the inverse of <Font bold="true">A</Font>.</Font> </Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">To do this, we can use the <Font bold="true">Gauss-Jordan Elimination Function</Font> seen below:</Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group hide-input="false" labelreference="L123" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">GaussJordanEliminationFunction:=proc(M::Matrix)
local d1,d2,J;
d1:=RowDimension(M);
d2:=ColumnDimension(M);
J:=IdentityMatrix(d1);
if d1=d2 then return ReducedRowEchelonForm(&lt;M|J&gt;) else printf(&quot;Error: Must use Square Matrix!&quot;) end if
end proc</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output><Text-field style="2D Output" layout="Maple Output"><Equation executable="false" style="2D Output" display=""></Equation></Text-field>
</Output>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L129" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">What this function does is: </Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L156" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bullet="dot">First, the function determines the row and column dimension of a given matrix M and labels their values with d1 and d2 respectively. </Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bullet="dot">Then it forms an identity matrix of equal dimension. </Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bullet="dot">Then the function checks whether d1=d2, the row and column dimensions are equal. </Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bullet="dot">If they are not equal it will return an error message. </Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bullet="dot">If they are equal then the function augments the matrix with the identity matrix of equal dimension and then reduces the augmented matrix to row echelon form.</Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bullet="dot">Finally the function returns the reduced matrix and terminates. 
 </Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group hide-input="false" labelreference="L124" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
