<Output><Text-field style="2D Output" layout="Maple Output"><Equation executable="false" style="2D Output" display=""></Equation></Text-field>
</Output>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L131" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field><Text-field style="Text" opaque="true" size="16" background="[255,204,153]" layout="Normal"><Font opaque="true" size="16" background="[255,204,153]">Question 3) Write a Maple procedure RowOperation1(A,p,q) which should take as input any matrix <Font bold="true">A</Font> (of arbitrary size m cross n) and two integers p and q, and return the matrix <Font bold="true">A</Font> with the pth and qth rows swapped. </Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Text" opaque="true" background="[255,204,153]" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group hide-input="false" labelreference="L132" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">RowOperation1:=proc(A::Matrix,p,q)::Matrix;
local d1,d2,Rp,Rq;
d1:=RowDimension(A);
d2:=ColumnDimension(A);
if (p&lt;=0 or q&lt;=0) then printf(&quot;Error: Please choose values of p and q that are non-negative&quot;);
elif (p&gt;d1 or q &gt; d1) then printf(&quot;Error: Please choose values of p and q that do not exceed the row dimensions of the matrix.&quot;) else Rp:=A[p,1..d2];Rq:=A[q,1..d2];
A[q,1..d2]:=Rp; A[p,1..d2]:=Rq;
return A;
end if;
end proc</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output><Text-field style="2D Output" layout="Maple Output"><Equation executable="false" style="2D Output" display=""></Equation></Text-field>
</Output>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L136" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"><Font bold="true">What this function does is:</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L155" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bullet="dot">First the function defines the row and column dimension and labels them d1 and d2 respectively. </Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bullet="dot">If p or q exceed the row dimension then the function returns an error message and terminateds. </Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bullet="dot">If p or q do not exceed the row dimension then the function defines the pth and qth row as Rp and Rq respectively. </Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bullet="dot">Then it redefines the matrix's pth row as Rq and qth row as Rp, effectively switching their position. </Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bullet="dot">Then it returns the matrix <Font bold="true">A</Font> with row operation and terminates.

See below for the function in use:</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
