<Group labelreference="L153" drawlabel="true" applyint="true" applyrational="true" applyexponent="false">
<Input><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bulletsuffix="." bullet="dot">Find the row and column dimension of a given Matrix <Font mathvariant="bold" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" fontweight="bold" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" bold="true" mathcolor="[0,0,0]">A.</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bulletsuffix="." bullet="dot"><Font mathvariant="normal" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" mathcolor="[0,0,0]">If the input p or q are less than or equal to 0, the function prints an error message and terminates.</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bulletsuffix="." bullet="dot">If the input p or q aren't less than or equal to 0, the function checks to see if p or q are greater than the row dimension of <Font mathvariant="bold" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" fontweight="bold" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" bold="true" mathcolor="[0,0,0]">A</Font><Font mathvariant="normal" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" mathcolor="[0,0,0]">.</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bulletsuffix="." bullet="dot">If p or q are greater than the row dimension of <Font mathvariant="bold" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" fontweight="bold" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" bold="true" mathcolor="[0,0,0]">A</Font><Font mathvariant="normal" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" mathcolor="[0,0,0]">, the function prints an error message and terminates. </Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bulletsuffix="." bullet="dot">If p or q aren't greater than the row dimension of <Font mathvariant="bold" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" fontweight="bold" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" bold="true" mathcolor="[0,0,0]">A</Font><Font mathvariant="normal" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" mathcolor="[0,0,0]">, the function then checks to see if p=q.</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bulletsuffix="." bullet="dot">If p=q then the function defines Rp as the pth row of <Font mathvariant="bold" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" fontweight="bold" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" bold="true" mathcolor="[0,0,0]">A</Font><Font mathvariant="normal" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" mathcolor="[0,0,0]"> and then redefines the pth row of  </Font><Font mathvariant="bold" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" fontweight="bold" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" bold="true" mathcolor="[0,0,0]">A </Font><Font mathvariant="normal" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" mathcolor="[0,0,0]">to be Rp divided by the input x.</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bulletsuffix="." bullet="dot">If p=/=q then the function defines Rp as the pth row and Rq as the qth row of <Font mathvariant="bold" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" fontweight="bold" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" bold="true" mathcolor="[0,0,0]">A</Font><Font mathvariant="normal" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" mathcolor="[0,0,0]"> and then redefines the pth row of  </Font><Font mathvariant="bold" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" fontweight="bold" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" bold="true" mathcolor="[0,0,0]">A</Font><Font mathvariant="normal" mathbackground="[255,255,255]" mathsize="12" fontfamily="Times New Roman" mathcolor="[0,0,0]"> as Rp-x*Rq.</Font></Text-field><Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal" bulletsuffix="." bullet="dot">Finally, the function returns the augmented matrix and terminates. 
</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
